columns.text:
**Exchange rate** is the value of a country's currency when expressed in another country's currency. A forward trade is an agreement to exchange currency in the future. The exchange rate in the agreement of a forward trade is called a forward exchange rate.

&nbsp;

The **spot rate** is the exchange rate in a spot trade. The **spot trade** is an agreement to exchange currencies based on the exchange rate on that date and must be settled within two business days.

First, we will invest Kr 1. We will determine the value of 1 Norwegian Krone after 180 days. The computation is as follows:
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{$F_{180}$} &=\text{KR 1}\times{\text{[1+($R_{FC}$}})]^{180/365}\\
 &=\text{Kr 1}\times{\text{[1+0.057}}]^{180/365}\\
 &=\text{Kr 1}\times{\text{[1.057}}]^{180/365}\\
 &=\text{Kr 1}\times{\text{1.0277}}\\
&=\boxed{\text{Kr 1.0277}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
Supposed we have invest KR 1. After six months, its value will be **KR 1.0277.**

Next, we need to determine the value of Kr 1 in dollar using the spot rate. The computation is as follows:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Value in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Kr 1 }}{\text{Spot Rate}}\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\text{Kr 1 }}{\text{Kr 8.39}}\\[10pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 0.1192}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
The value of Kr 1 in U.S. dollar using the spot exchange rate is **$0.1192**.

Next, we will determine the value of the U.S. dollar after 6 months using the value of spot exchange rate.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{$F_{180}$} &=\text{\$ 0.1192}\times{\text{[1+($R_{US}$}})]^{180/365}\\[10pt]
 &=\text{\$ 0.1192}\times{\text{[1+0.038}}]^{180/365}\\[10pt]
 &=\text{\$ 0.1192}\times{\text{[1.038}}]^{180/365}\\[10pt]
 &=\text{\$ 0.1192}\times{\text{1.0186}}\\
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 0.1214}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
The Kr 1, when converted into dollars, the value after six months will be **$ 0.1214.**

The formula of the interest rate parity is as follows:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{$F_{t}$} &=\text{$S_{0}$}\times{\text{[1+($R_{FC}$}-{\text{$R_{US}$}}})]^t\\[10pt]
\end{aligned}$$

Where: &nbsp;
$F_{t}$ =  forward exchange rate for settlement at a given time &nbsp;
$R_{US}$ = Nominal risk-free rate of U.S. &nbsp;
$R_{FC}$ = Nominal risk-free rate of a foreign country &nbsp;
$S_{0}$ = Spot Exchange Rate
